Subject: [PATCH] ui: register fennec://setup and SetupPageHandler

Registers the fennec://setup WebUI page and its C++ handler:
  FennecSetupUI   — WebUIController, serves the React bundle
  SetupPageHandler — Mojo handler, bridges window.__fennec.setup.commit()
                     to C++ profile initialisation

On setup completion, SetupPageHandler::HandleCommit():
  1. Writes the user's consent choices to profile prefs
  2. Calls ReleaseConsentGuard() (consent-first-no-boot-requests.patch)
  3. Enables any opted-in services (filter list updates, Mods registry)
  4. Sets prefs::kFennecSetupCompleted = true
  5. Navigates to fennec://newtab

The setup page is shown on first launch only. Subsequent launches
skip it (kFennecSetupCompleted check in ChromeBrowserMainParts).

TODO: Stub for the C++ handler. React UI is already implemented in
      src/ui/setup/. Full handler wiring tracked: fennec-browser/fennec#19

PILLAR: Transparency / Calm UI
JOURNAL: After consent is granted and the guard is released, this handler
         fires one kFennecInternal event "setup-complete" in the Journal.
